snippet.textDisplay: Gurdas mann ji without any doubt is a gem, legend and pride of punjab. No words to appreciate him. But I'm really surprised with the appearance of Diljeet in this song. And moreover, with his singing, He's known to sing hip-hop, rap (jatt style) punjabi songs but first time he has sing something so good that actually I'm now finding another gurdaas mann in him. If diljeet changes his genre and leave that music which he was known to sing till now and sing such punjabi cultural songs. He will surely reach on top one day. Great combination. God bless them both.

snippet.textDisplay: Wow!!! What a song this is. Surely, gonna be one of my all time favourite of Coke Studio @MTV. A song filled with grace and love for one's culture and tradition. Couldn't understand thoroughly but little with subtitles. This song doesn't only talk about the Punjabi culture but it is the representative voice of every culture that is going through massive acculturation and losing its significance at the hand of imported cultures. What a pleasure to listen to Gurdas Maan as alwasy. He is one of the very few people I have seen on this planet who loves what he does and all he loves is his 'MUSIC'. Hats off to him for creating wonders through this song....I would listen this again and again...
